1
00:00:48,167 --> 00:00:51,033
[Episode 15]

2
00:00:51,033 --> 00:00:53,600
If you go to the palace gate
as Gil Dong, you'll die.

3
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:55,667
But you're still going?

4
00:00:58,300 --> 00:00:59,700
Then I'm going too.

5
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,433
Mister.

6
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:04,433
I'll go too.

7
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:06,033
I'm going too.

8
00:01:06,033 --> 00:01:08,667
Please let me go too.

9
00:01:08,667 --> 00:01:10,033
- Me too.
- We'll go too.

10
00:01:10,033 --> 00:01:11,300
- I'll go too.
- I'm going too.

11
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:15,267
- I'll go too.
- Me too!

12
00:01:33,967 --> 00:01:37,600
There is somewhere I must go first.

13
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:41,067
Are you saying His Majesty has been
poisoned with the poisonous herb?

14
00:01:41,067 --> 00:01:45,300
Yes, Your Highness. Please inform
the ministers and gather their support,

15
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:48,533
and spread the proclamations
as far as possible.

16
00:01:49,567 --> 00:01:52,467
[The king, deceived by treacherous ministers,
took poison and went mad]

17
00:01:52,467 --> 00:01:55,600
Everyone in this land must know it.

18
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:58,867
I will summon our troops.

19
00:01:58,867 --> 00:02:01,267
It will take days to reach the capital,

20
00:02:01,267 --> 00:02:03,433
but you must wait until then...

21
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:08,967
You have to go now, right?

22
00:02:08,967 --> 00:02:11,000
It will be okay.

23
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,967
Because I'm not alone.

24
00:02:14,467 --> 00:02:16,900
It will be a deep, dark night.

25
00:02:19,067 --> 00:02:21,733
Let's meet in a new Joseon.

26
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,167
Gil Dong is here.

27
00:02:32,167 --> 00:02:34,500
He came knowing it would cost him his life.

28
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:36,800
He must be out of his mind.

29
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:39,800
Who would risk their life
for a woman like that?

30
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,900
They say he even stole rice for her.

31
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:46,100
She lost everything, had nothing to eat,
and her milk dried up.

32
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:48,500
Oh dear, that's pitiful.

33
00:02:49,267 --> 00:02:52,833
If such a heart is a crime,
then bind me as well.

34
00:02:52,833 --> 00:02:55,000
Then I shall demand to be bound too.

35
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Me too.

36
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,833
- Me too.
- Me too.

37
00:02:57,833 --> 00:03:00,667
We may not be like Gil Dong,

38
00:03:00,667 --> 00:03:04,500
but can't we at least do something ourselves?

39
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:06,867
Yes, yes.

40
00:03:07,868 --> 00:03:11,163
- That's right.
- Exactly.

41
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:21,900
<i>The name Gil Dong was too grand for me.</i>

42
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:27,100
<i>The name righteous thief was even more so.</i>

43
00:03:27,100 --> 00:03:31,233
Oh, sorry.

44
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:37,333
How can she take such
bitter medicine on an empty stomach?

45
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:40,333
<i>I was just a nosy court physician.</i>

46
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:43,567
<i>I was neither more nor less.</i>

47
00:03:43,567 --> 00:03:45,367
But he's even stranger than I thought.

48
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:48,700
<i>If it weren't for Gil Dong,
our fates would never have intertwined.</i>

49
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:50,344
From now on,

50
00:03:50,344 --> 00:03:52,100
stay within my reach.

51
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:55,433
Only as far as I can embrace.

52
00:03:55,433 --> 00:03:56,733
<i>Grand Prince.</i>

53
00:03:56,733 --> 00:03:59,600
<i>He watched over my thievery,</i>

54
00:04:01,167 --> 00:04:03,333
<i>and for what I wanted to protect,</i>

55
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:05,600
<i>he fought by becoming me,</i>

56
00:04:06,267 --> 00:04:09,867
<i>and in that time, I became him,</i>

57
00:04:11,367 --> 00:04:14,000
<i>harboring a different heart.</i>

58
00:04:21,033 --> 00:04:22,033
<i>Treasonous intent.</i>

59
00:04:22,033 --> 00:04:23,467
Poisonous herb?

60
00:04:23,467 --> 00:04:24,867
How could this happen?

61
00:04:24,867 --> 00:04:26,833
This is unbelievable.

62
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:30,000
<i>Thus, it's a coup.</i>

63
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:33,576
[Ming Silk and Broad Wood]

64
00:04:34,233 --> 00:04:38,033
<i>And if such a moment ever came,</i>

65
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:41,633
<i>I vowed I would never hesitate.</i>

66
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:44,100
Then what about me?

67
00:04:44,100 --> 00:04:47,333
What should I do in a tomorrow without you?

68
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:50,200
<i>But why does that moment come to mind now?</i>

69
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:51,400
Let's run away.

70
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:54,533
If you're caught as a rebel, you'll be
torn limb from limb while still alive.

71
00:04:54,533 --> 00:04:56,000
I'm prepared for that.

72
00:04:56,000 --> 00:05:00,567
<i>Why do I see his disheartened face only now?</i>

73
00:05:00,567 --> 00:05:04,900
How can you speak of dying
so casually before me?

74
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:08,400
<i>Only tonight does that look
in his eyes overwhelm me.</i>

75
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:11,333
<i>What am I supposed to do?</i>

76
00:05:11,333 --> 00:05:14,200
Hong Eun Jo, I...

77
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:15,933
I know.

78
00:05:19,233 --> 00:05:20,933
I...

79
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:29,233
I know everything.

80
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:32,467
<i>If tomorrow comes for me...</i>

81
00:05:33,267 --> 00:05:35,000
I'll go.

82
00:05:37,100 --> 00:05:39,133
We shall meet again.

83
00:05:43,933 --> 00:05:46,733
<i>Then I will say the words I swallowed today</i>

84
00:05:46,733 --> 00:05:48,633
<i>without fail.</i>

85
00:05:57,467 --> 00:06:05,167
<i>♫ If time would stop,
the warm touch of my hand ♫</i>

86
00:06:05,167 --> 00:06:11,867
<i>♫ If I could pass it to you again ♫</i>

87
00:06:11,867 --> 00:06:19,533
<i>♫ Swallowing my tears,
even drenched in longing ♫</i>

88
00:06:19,533 --> 00:06:25,400
<i>♫ I will just look on ♫</i>

89
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:28,967
<i>♫ Forever ♫</i>

90
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:34,300
<i>♫ The moonlight falling quietly ♫</i>

91
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:41,467
<i>♫ Only illuminates your traces ♫</i>

92
00:06:41,467 --> 00:06:48,600
<i>♫ Even trying to embrace you,
I cannot reach ♫</i>

93
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:56,633
<i>♫ My heart, burned pure white,
cannot be undone ♫</i>

94
00:06:56,633 --> 00:07:04,267
<i>♫ If time would stop,
the warm touch of my hand ♫</i>

95
00:07:04,267 --> 00:07:11,000
<i>♫ If I could pass it to you again ♫</i>

96
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:18,600
<i>♫ Even as tears flow, drenched in longing ♫</i>

97
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:21,233
<i>♫ I will just look on ♫</i>

98
00:07:21,233 --> 00:07:23,733
I'll lure them out of the alley.

99
00:07:25,867 --> 00:07:29,867
If it were the old me,
I would have listened to those words.

100
00:07:29,867 --> 00:07:33,633
But now, I can't even hear them.

101
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:36,667
I won't run away anymore.

102
00:07:43,633 --> 00:07:47,167
One, two.

103
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:59,667
It seems you've come out to greet me.

104
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:05,033
You are Min Jik's...

105
00:08:06,133 --> 00:08:08,233
Why are the two of you here?

106
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:10,933
We were on our way to see Your Majesty.

107
00:08:10,933 --> 00:08:14,033
With something meant for Your Majesty.

108
00:08:15,467 --> 00:08:17,133
Meant for me?

109
00:08:17,133 --> 00:08:20,567
I mean, Yeonsuk Flower.

110
00:08:20,567 --> 00:08:22,467
What is that?

111
00:08:25,933 --> 00:08:28,800
You didn't even know its name?

112
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:32,100
Your Majesty! Your Majesty!

113
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,100
What is the matter?

114
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:34,500
You must go down that street.

115
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:37,000
- Gil Dong is...
- After him!

116
00:08:39,131 --> 00:08:41,300
Hyah!

117
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:43,400
Gil Dong has been captured.

118
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:51,233
Where is Gil Dong?

119
00:08:51,233 --> 00:08:53,767
We are searching for him, Your Majesty.

120
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,600
What happened?

121
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,633
We are trying to ascertain the situation.

122
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:01,600
Stop this at once.

123
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:06,567
Hong Eun Jo.

124
00:09:22,433 --> 00:09:24,600
What

125
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,333
is this?

126
00:09:38,233 --> 00:09:40,633
Butcher's masks?

127
00:09:40,633 --> 00:09:45,533
Yes, butcher's masks are hung up
everywhere in the marketplace.

128
00:09:45,533 --> 00:09:47,033
What does that mean?

129
00:09:47,033 --> 00:09:50,833
Is it a sign of showing support for Gil Dong?

130
00:09:54,433 --> 00:09:55,867
It's too early to celebrate.

131
00:09:55,867 --> 00:09:59,867
It has spread throughout the entire capital.

132
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:21,267
How could this...

133
00:10:32,133 --> 00:10:34,967
Drag out and kill all

134
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:37,700
who hang those masks!

135
00:10:38,933 --> 00:10:41,600
All of them?

136
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,800
They are innocent citizens.

137
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:47,667
If they claim to be Gil Dong,
then they are Gil Dong.

138
00:10:51,533 --> 00:10:55,433
Your Majesty, it's a notice
written by Gil Dong.

139
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,933
Read it.

140
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:02,367
I cannot bring myself to say it aloud...

141
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:09,733
The king was deceived by a traitor
and took a poisonous herb.

142
00:11:09,733 --> 00:11:11,000
Insolent!

143
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,467
And he went mad.

144
00:11:18,633 --> 00:11:20,328
Yeonsuk Flower

145
00:11:20,328 --> 00:11:24,067
is the name of the poison
planted inside Your Majesty's body.

146
00:11:25,067 --> 00:11:28,000
Are you even aware of your madness?

147
00:11:47,467 --> 00:11:49,567
It's here.

148
00:11:54,167 --> 00:11:56,400
Drive out the tiger!

149
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:57,896
Hyah!

150
00:11:57,896 --> 00:11:59,336
Hyah.

151
00:12:00,488 --> 00:12:01,864
Hyah.

152
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:04,700
He is seeing hallucinations.

153
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,700
If we let His Majesty
roam the streets like this,

154
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:09,433
the people will be hunted down.

155
00:12:09,433 --> 00:12:11,464
We must guide him
along the least crowded paths

156
00:12:11,464 --> 00:12:13,333
and drive him back to the palace.

157
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:17,433
Chase him eastward,
follow the city wall north,

158
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:22,100
pass Inwangsan and Baegaksan Mountain,
and enter through Shinmu Gate.

159
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:23,933
Follow His Highness' orders!

160
00:12:23,933 --> 00:12:26,200
- Yes.
- Yes.

161
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:28,000
Let's go together.

162
00:12:33,967 --> 00:12:35,700
[Royal Investigative Bureau]
Jae Yi.

163
00:12:38,067 --> 00:12:39,567
Is there a Gil Dong who was brought
to the Royal Investigative Bureau?

164
00:12:39,567 --> 00:12:43,133
He's flashing everywhere.
How could they catch him?

165
00:12:44,367 --> 00:12:46,300
Understood.

166
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:47,688
You

167
00:12:47,688 --> 00:12:49,633
haven't seen it yet, have you?

168
00:12:49,633 --> 00:12:51,048
Seen what?

169
00:12:51,803 --> 00:12:54,504
[The king, deceived by treacherous ministers,
took poison and went mad]

170
00:12:56,167 --> 00:12:58,467
<i>Is it related to the incident
at the royal bedchamber?</i>

171
00:12:58,467 --> 00:13:01,367
I will wait here for His Majesty's judgment.

172
00:13:02,400 --> 00:13:04,900
Find out immediately where my father is.

173
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:08,100
Just confess now.

174
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:10,667
I know nothing about it.

175
00:13:10,667 --> 00:13:12,100
Do you have evidence?

176
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:13,800
Yes.

177
00:13:16,867 --> 00:13:20,167
Evidence, and a witness.

178
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:28,967
How splendid.

179
00:13:28,967 --> 00:13:34,100
If this is your evidence, it must be
the poison brought into the royal chamber.

180
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:37,933
Where is the witness?

181
00:13:37,933 --> 00:13:39,633
Here, Lady Suk Yong
has confessed everything...

182
00:13:39,633 --> 00:13:42,700
Such a lowly creature can't be a witness.

183
00:13:44,233 --> 00:13:46,467
Is she not a beast?

184
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:50,967
This is the scheme of that beast.

185
00:13:54,933 --> 00:13:58,967
The exalted Left State Councilor
shifted blame onto a woman?

186
00:13:58,967 --> 00:14:01,167
What a disgrace to a man.

187
00:14:03,767 --> 00:14:07,667
Whether she can be a witness
or not is not up to the ministers.

188
00:14:11,367 --> 00:14:13,067
Have you forgotten?

189
00:14:13,067 --> 00:14:16,833
The one who now fills
the main hall with ministers,

190
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:20,000
is me.

191
00:14:23,567 --> 00:14:26,267
They are essentially my extensions.

192
00:14:26,267 --> 00:14:29,133
Extensions of this treacherous minister.

193
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:33,033
They care nothing for responsibility.

194
00:14:33,033 --> 00:14:35,800
Only for their own gain.

195
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:38,733
Shameless people, indeed.

196
00:14:38,733 --> 00:14:40,233
The safety of the nation is at stake.

197
00:14:40,233 --> 00:14:41,400
We must make a decision.

198
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:42,667
It's too rash.

199
00:14:42,667 --> 00:14:45,233
If we fail, we become rebels.

200
00:14:45,233 --> 00:14:48,367
Of course, we must be cautious.

201
00:14:48,367 --> 00:14:53,700
The Left State Councilor has not
even admitted the poison exists, right?

202
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:56,033
How dare you!

203
00:14:56,033 --> 00:14:59,500
Persuading the ministers does not seem easy.

204
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:03,100
Did you truly expect righteousness
from Im Sa Hyeong's puppets?

205
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:04,800
Is this what you anticipated?

206
00:15:04,800 --> 00:15:06,967
The moral cause already stands with us.

207
00:15:06,967 --> 00:15:08,067
What about the soldiers?

208
00:15:08,067 --> 00:15:10,800
They will arrive by morning at the earliest.

209
00:15:11,867 --> 00:15:15,367
The gate guards we recruited
have agreed to open the gates.

210
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:19,667
Head straight to the palace
without delay and behead the king.

211
00:15:19,667 --> 00:15:23,633
If necessary, kill the ministers
as well to prevent future trouble.

212
00:15:23,633 --> 00:15:26,367
Gil Dong and the Grand Prince
do not wish for a bloody conflict.

213
00:15:26,367 --> 00:15:28,800
If we are not careful, even the people
heading to the marketplace will be in danger.

214
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:31,167
A bloodless entry is a foolish dream.

215
00:15:31,167 --> 00:15:33,867
No throne exists without bloodshed.

216
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:37,700
The bloodstains

217
00:15:38,533 --> 00:15:41,667
will dry when the new sun rises.

218
00:15:43,167 --> 00:15:45,000
Let's go to the palace!

219
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,856
- They're going?
- Right now?

220
00:15:46,856 --> 00:15:50,312
They're leaving for the palace.

221
00:15:54,728 --> 00:15:56,200
If it's the palace...

222
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:57,448
Let's go together!

223
00:15:57,448 --> 00:15:58,952
We should go too.

224
00:16:00,233 --> 00:16:01,767
What about your condition?

225
00:16:01,767 --> 00:16:03,400
I'm fine.

226
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:06,900
It wouldn't feel right if we weren't
part of Gil Dong's story.

227
00:16:09,967 --> 00:16:11,800
Let's go!

228
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,896
Let's go!

229
00:16:13,896 --> 00:16:20,667
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

230
00:16:25,967 --> 00:16:27,633
What about the other women
of the Inner Court Registry?

231
00:16:27,633 --> 00:16:30,767
They have all been sent out of the palace
under the pretext of refuge.

232
00:16:30,767 --> 00:16:32,467
All done.

233
00:16:36,533 --> 00:16:39,000
Please depart quickly, Your Majesty.

234
00:16:39,767 --> 00:16:43,167
Why is there only one palanquin?

235
00:16:46,233 --> 00:16:47,633
It can't be.

236
00:16:47,633 --> 00:16:50,200
If that is the case,
I will remain in the palace as well.

237
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:52,533
If the content of the posters is true,

238
00:16:52,533 --> 00:16:55,867
we do not know what acts
His Majesty's madness might commit.

239
00:16:55,867 --> 00:16:58,567
Your Majesty must protect the Crown Prince.

240
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:01,133
Your Majesty!

241
00:17:04,633 --> 00:17:07,433
A mother must protect her child.

242
00:17:07,433 --> 00:17:10,633
I too am staying to protect my child.

243
00:17:13,533 --> 00:17:15,267
Hurry.

244
00:17:15,267 --> 00:17:18,568
You must survive this night safely.

245
00:17:19,196 --> 00:17:21,384
Hyah!

246
00:17:25,563 --> 00:17:27,388
Hyah!

247
00:17:37,133 --> 00:17:39,333
It's the tiger, Your Majesty.

248
00:17:51,167 --> 00:17:53,400
This way, Your Majesty!

249
00:17:55,048 --> 00:17:56,296
Hyah!

250
00:17:56,296 --> 00:17:57,800
Hyah!

251
00:17:59,633 --> 00:18:02,500
Your Majesty, it's here!

252
00:18:09,667 --> 00:18:11,367
It's this way.

253
00:18:12,123 --> 00:18:13,947
Hyah!

254
00:18:17,500 --> 00:18:19,233
It's over there.

255
00:18:24,133 --> 00:18:25,867
This way.

256
00:18:27,733 --> 00:18:29,467
Over there.

257
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,267
It's the tiger, Your Majesty!

258
00:18:38,108 --> 00:18:39,995
Hyah!

259
00:18:41,667 --> 00:18:43,433
This way.

260
00:18:45,563 --> 00:18:47,035
Hyah!

261
00:18:51,133 --> 00:18:53,433
Open the gate!

262
00:19:08,267 --> 00:19:11,100
When did I enter the palace?

263
00:19:46,867 --> 00:19:49,400
Did you trick me?

264
00:19:51,433 --> 00:19:53,667
Someone!

265
00:19:53,667 --> 00:19:56,267
Drag the Grand Prince out!

266
00:20:01,367 --> 00:20:04,033
Where have you hidden the soldiers?

267
00:20:07,633 --> 00:20:12,433
So, you aimed for the throne.

268
00:20:13,233 --> 00:20:16,200
I should have seen your true colors

269
00:20:16,200 --> 00:20:19,033
back in Gyeongo Year.

270
00:20:19,033 --> 00:20:22,767
Mother, Mother!

271
00:20:24,867 --> 00:20:26,600
Mother.

272
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:32,700
This time, who will follow my father
to the afterlife?

273
00:20:39,567 --> 00:20:41,633
Stop it.

274
00:20:42,467 --> 00:20:44,433
Will you die in their place?

275
00:20:44,433 --> 00:20:47,433
Can you handle the aftermath?

276
00:20:47,433 --> 00:20:48,900
The Crown Prince is young,

277
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:51,933
and by killing the only remaining bloodline,
you jeopardize the royal lineage.

278
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:57,333
For the ministers cast aside, there could
be no better justification for a coup.

279
00:20:57,333 --> 00:20:58,600
You wretch!

280
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:01,333
You told me not to shine,
so I walked only in the shadows.

281
00:21:01,333 --> 00:21:05,133
And you told me not to be seen
by the world, so I walked alone.

282
00:21:06,033 --> 00:21:08,600
Let me continue living that way.

283
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:13,167
Your Majesty, please also do nothing,

284
00:21:13,167 --> 00:21:15,967
meaning harm no one.

285
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:25,400
That night,

286
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:28,633
I should have drawn my sword.

287
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:35,167
With this sword,

288
00:21:35,167 --> 00:21:38,067
I should have cut you down.

289
00:22:01,900 --> 00:22:06,133
[Injeongmun Gate]

290
00:22:49,700 --> 00:22:51,733
Rebels!

291
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:05,767
Must I truly put a blade
to your throat, Brother?

292
00:23:05,767 --> 00:23:07,600
You scoundrel!

293
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:59,433
What you see now is not real.

294
00:24:01,867 --> 00:24:03,912
Then

295
00:24:03,912 --> 00:24:06,500
what is that?

296
00:24:13,033 --> 00:24:14,567
Look closely.

297
00:24:14,567 --> 00:24:17,067
It is not the shape of a tiger.

298
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:21,480
No,

299
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:23,867
that can't be.

300
00:24:24,700 --> 00:24:26,667
It can't be.

301
00:24:37,600 --> 00:24:39,333
It can't be.

302
00:24:44,667 --> 00:24:46,376
Then

303
00:24:46,376 --> 00:24:48,800
what I have been chasing all this time

304
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:50,600
was an illusion?

305
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:52,633
It was delusion.

306
00:24:54,600 --> 00:25:00,100
Do you know how you came to this state?

307
00:25:02,733 --> 00:25:04,808
It is because

308
00:25:04,808 --> 00:25:08,300
Your Majesty abandoned your duty.

309
00:25:08,300 --> 00:25:10,667
My duty?

310
00:25:10,667 --> 00:25:12,456
Your Majesty,

311
00:25:12,456 --> 00:25:14,833
more than anyone in this country,

312
00:25:14,833 --> 00:25:18,000
should have regarded
the people with compassion.

313
00:25:20,333 --> 00:25:23,133
They are Your Majesty's people.

314
00:25:23,133 --> 00:25:25,533
Please have pity on them.

315
00:25:25,533 --> 00:25:27,272
That is

316
00:25:27,272 --> 00:25:32,167
the responsibility and qualification
of the one who sits the throne.

317
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:36,667
Punishing them for petitions alone

318
00:25:36,667 --> 00:25:39,900
will bring great misfortune
to Your Majesty in the future.

319
00:25:39,900 --> 00:25:42,567
If my father spoke candidly to Your Majesty,

320
00:25:42,567 --> 00:25:47,533
all his words were solely
for Your Majesty's sake.

321
00:25:47,533 --> 00:25:51,567
Please do not forget the sincerity
that drove him to Your Majesty

322
00:25:51,567 --> 00:25:53,567
even at the cost of his life.

323
00:26:10,933 --> 00:26:12,633
Right.

324
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:18,267
Hong Min Jik...

325
00:26:18,267 --> 00:26:21,100
Min Jik has returned!

326
00:26:37,480 --> 00:26:38,500
[Jeongwiheon Pavilion]

327
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:40,433
A royal command, is it?

328
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:45,633
Alright.

329
00:26:45,633 --> 00:26:47,467
Tell us at once.

330
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:50,867
There is no royal command.

331
00:26:52,433 --> 00:26:53,533
Write this down.

332
00:26:53,533 --> 00:26:55,400
I, Im Jae Yi, the second son of Im Sa Hyeong,

333
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:59,300
purchased poison to bring into
the bedchamber under my father's orders.

334
00:26:59,300 --> 00:27:01,267
It's a lie.

335
00:27:02,600 --> 00:27:04,567
Arrest me.

336
00:27:04,567 --> 00:27:07,500
As it is the testimony of the son
of the esteemed Left State Councilor,

337
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:10,867
no further witnesses are needed, correct?

338
00:27:10,867 --> 00:27:12,100
Lock him up in prison!

339
00:27:12,100 --> 00:27:13,800
Yes!

340
00:27:14,933 --> 00:27:16,033
Let go!

341
00:27:16,033 --> 00:27:17,267
It's over now!

342
00:27:17,267 --> 00:27:19,800
You scoundrels!

343
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:22,833
I will see His Majesty!

344
00:27:22,833 --> 00:27:25,433
I will go to the main hall immediately!

345
00:27:29,148 --> 00:27:33,416
[Injeongmun Gate]

346
00:27:37,133 --> 00:27:40,700
What will happen now?

347
00:27:55,700 --> 00:27:57,700
Look.

348
00:27:57,700 --> 00:28:00,233
Dawn is breaking.

349
00:28:51,333 --> 00:28:54,133
Has Prince Yi Yeol already
returned from his place of refuge?

350
00:28:55,267 --> 00:28:56,500
Where is he now?

351
00:28:56,500 --> 00:28:58,233
Where?

352
00:29:09,700 --> 00:29:13,533
Let me see. Are you alright?

353
00:29:15,567 --> 00:29:18,000
Yes, Your Majesty.

354
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:20,533
Why do you not jest?

355
00:29:20,533 --> 00:29:23,033
Why do you not smile slyly as you used to?

356
00:29:30,700 --> 00:29:33,767
It must be worn out and frayed,
like these socks.

357
00:29:34,933 --> 00:29:37,533
The care you've shown me all this time.

358
00:29:41,767 --> 00:29:43,500
Mother.

359
00:29:43,500 --> 00:29:45,933
I should stop playing now.

360
00:29:46,800 --> 00:29:48,833
They say it is abdication.

361
00:29:48,833 --> 00:29:50,600
[Abdication: The king passes
the throne to another]

362
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:52,133
It's a bloodless entry.

363
00:29:52,133 --> 00:29:54,800
Even before the soldiers arrived.

364
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:57,000
Abdication?

365
00:29:57,000 --> 00:29:58,900
I was wrong.

366
00:29:58,900 --> 00:30:02,733
Gil Dong and the Grand Prince,
those two were right.

367
00:30:09,567 --> 00:30:11,300
Eun Jo!

368
00:30:16,367 --> 00:30:18,133
Lady Hae Rim?

369
00:30:22,333 --> 00:30:24,133
Eun Jo!

370
00:30:24,133 --> 00:30:25,200
Eun Jo.

371
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,900
Physician Hong.

372
00:30:27,700 --> 00:30:28,904
Physician Hong!

373
00:30:28,904 --> 00:30:30,400
Yeah.

374
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:32,167
I'm here too.

375
00:30:32,933 --> 00:30:34,533
- Physician Hong!
- Physician Hong!

376
00:30:34,533 --> 00:30:36,700
- Eun Jo!
- It's the physician!

377
00:30:36,700 --> 00:30:38,667
- Physician!
- Eun Jo!

378
00:30:38,667 --> 00:30:42,033
- Physician!
- Physician Hong!

379
00:30:42,033 --> 00:30:45,100
How is everyone...

380
00:30:45,100 --> 00:30:46,833
Look.

381
00:30:46,833 --> 00:30:49,067
Now, the sun finally rises.

382
00:31:28,933 --> 00:31:33,700
His Majesty the King arrives!

383
00:32:24,133 --> 00:32:27,467
Engrave this in your heart
whenever you walk the royal path.

384
00:32:27,467 --> 00:32:31,833
Every step a king takes
must be towards the people.

385
00:32:31,833 --> 00:32:35,533
I shall remember it well, Mother.

386
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:40,500
Kowtowing four times.

387
00:32:40,500 --> 00:32:42,700
First bow.

388
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:51,567
Second bow.

389
00:32:56,933 --> 00:32:59,033
Third bow.

390
00:33:08,533 --> 00:33:10,600
[Royal Investigative Bureau]
Fourth bow.

391
00:33:13,567 --> 00:33:14,777
[Slave]
In recent years,

392
00:33:14,777 --> 00:33:17,633
Joseon has been impoverished and chaotic

393
00:33:17,633 --> 00:33:20,767
under the treacherous minister
Im Sa Hyeong and a tyrannical ruler.

394
00:33:20,767 --> 00:33:24,067
Responsibility for this lies with me,
who overlooked their crimes,

395
00:33:24,067 --> 00:33:26,633
and with all the civil
and military officials gathered here.

396
00:33:30,467 --> 00:33:31,767
Yet

397
00:33:31,767 --> 00:33:36,867
in these troubled times, there was
one person who pitied the people.

398
00:33:38,767 --> 00:33:40,500
That is Gil Dong.

399
00:33:44,167 --> 00:33:45,467
Therefore, from this day forth,

400
00:33:45,467 --> 00:33:48,900
all those connected to Gil Dong are pardoned.

401
00:33:50,133 --> 00:33:52,500
But Your Majesty, Gil Dong is a thief...

402
00:33:52,500 --> 00:33:56,300
If anyone belittles him as a mere thief

403
00:33:56,300 --> 00:33:59,900
and slanders his heart,
which cares for the people,

404
00:33:59,900 --> 00:34:03,100
they undermine the benevolence
and righteousness of Joseon.

405
00:34:03,100 --> 00:34:05,233
Such a man is the true traitor.

406
00:34:07,700 --> 00:34:09,633
Answer me.

407
00:34:10,533 --> 00:34:14,867
- Your grace is boundless.
- Your grace is boundless.

408
00:34:21,867 --> 00:34:23,500
Eun Jo!

409
00:34:23,500 --> 00:34:24,667
Mother! Young master!

410
00:34:24,667 --> 00:34:25,900
Eun Jo!

411
00:34:25,900 --> 00:34:28,100
Oh dear, be careful.

412
00:34:28,100 --> 00:34:29,133
- Eun Jo!
- Young master, be careful!

413
00:34:29,133 --> 00:34:30,167
Eun Jo! Eun Jo!

414
00:34:30,167 --> 00:34:32,467
Oh, young master, breathe first.

415
00:34:32,467 --> 00:34:34,800
That is not what matters. Don't be startled.

416
00:34:34,800 --> 00:34:36,933
What is it?

417
00:34:36,933 --> 00:34:39,067
I heard on my way here

418
00:34:39,067 --> 00:34:42,684
that we have a new king.

419
00:34:42,684 --> 00:34:44,967
Oh.

420
00:34:44,967 --> 00:34:46,933
She's beside herself with shock.

421
00:34:46,933 --> 00:34:48,800
Now brace yourself.

422
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:49,833
For what?

423
00:34:49,833 --> 00:34:51,533
That king is

424
00:34:52,233 --> 00:34:54,600
Grand Prince Do Wol.

425
00:34:55,300 --> 00:34:57,633
When I heard it,

426
00:34:57,633 --> 00:34:59,233
my heart slammed into the ground.

427
00:34:59,233 --> 00:35:02,033
Then pick it back up.

428
00:35:02,033 --> 00:35:04,200
- Why this reaction?
- It's about time for dinner.

429
00:35:04,200 --> 00:35:05,400
Let's talk at home.

430
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:06,696
Shall we?

431
00:35:06,696 --> 00:35:12,233
By the way, have you really sorted out
all the trouble you caused?

432
00:35:12,233 --> 00:35:13,867
From what I heard, it seems so.

433
00:35:13,867 --> 00:35:14,900
What?

434
00:35:14,900 --> 00:35:16,600
Mother.

435
00:35:20,667 --> 00:35:22,733
Hey, wait for me.

436
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:27,933
I heard it yesterday
from the Minister of Personnel.

437
00:35:27,933 --> 00:35:32,200
He said His Majesty works
in the main hall every day.

438
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:34,400
According to the Deputy Commander
of the Military Training Command,

439
00:35:35,067 --> 00:35:39,300
His Majesty ordered the ministers
who've been taking salaries

440
00:35:39,300 --> 00:35:40,567
for wagging their tongues
to work to the bone.

441
00:35:40,567 --> 00:35:43,500
That is why officials of senior rank
can't even leave the court.

442
00:35:43,500 --> 00:35:48,333
No wonder no officials
have shown up at the gibang.

443
00:35:48,333 --> 00:35:50,600
It's all thanks to His Majesty.

444
00:35:53,667 --> 00:35:58,000
Don't you understand that if customers
stop coming, our income will dry up too?

445
00:36:00,733 --> 00:36:02,867
Since when did you care about state affairs?

446
00:36:02,867 --> 00:36:04,567
Sis.

447
00:36:04,567 --> 00:36:08,933
My concern for the king is born of loyalty.

448
00:36:08,933 --> 00:36:10,167
Wake up.

449
00:36:10,167 --> 00:36:13,500
His Majesty already has
someone destined for him.

450
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:22,000
Though you have confessed,

451
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:25,367
colluding with Im Sa Hyeong
to disrupt Joseon is a grave crime.

452
00:36:25,367 --> 00:36:28,133
I petitioned that leniency
should not be granted.

453
00:36:29,833 --> 00:36:34,733
Our new king has appointed
a truly loyal subject.

454
00:36:37,736 --> 00:36:40,967
I leave tomorrow.

455
00:36:41,967 --> 00:36:46,400
This is the last time.
Won't you at least say goodbye?

456
00:36:46,400 --> 00:36:49,367
I'm the woman you once loved,
if only for a short while.

457
00:36:50,867 --> 00:36:53,500
The person before me now is a criminal.

458
00:37:00,033 --> 00:37:03,333
Accept your punishment gracefully.

459
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:15,433
I am grateful.

460
00:37:17,736 --> 00:37:20,433
Once again, he leaves without hearing me out.

461
00:37:27,967 --> 00:37:29,433
That despicable fool, Kim Seung Baek.

462
00:37:29,433 --> 00:37:31,300
You got out of prison, and he
couldn't even show his face?

463
00:37:31,300 --> 00:37:32,733
Jeez.

464
00:37:32,733 --> 00:37:36,300
He thinks you're of no use to him.

465
00:37:41,867 --> 00:37:45,033
I've lived as the eldest son
of a ruined family, so I know how it is.

466
00:37:45,033 --> 00:37:50,167
Wherever you go, telling yourself
'I am an unwanted guest' makes it bearable.

467
00:37:50,967 --> 00:37:52,167
Is that supposed to comfort me?

468
00:37:52,167 --> 00:37:53,900
Doesn't it work?

469
00:37:55,200 --> 00:37:57,600
Hong Eun Jo told me to take good care of you.

470
00:38:00,867 --> 00:38:03,033
Go tell her

471
00:38:03,033 --> 00:38:05,100
I look perfectly fine

472
00:38:07,567 --> 00:38:09,467
that I even manage to smile.

473
00:38:15,700 --> 00:38:18,200
Why did you abandon everything?

474
00:38:19,467 --> 00:38:22,333
The things you bestowed upon me,

475
00:38:23,300 --> 00:38:26,000
I never truly possessed them.

476
00:38:28,967 --> 00:38:33,600
If you discard what I gave you,
you are nothing.

477
00:38:34,767 --> 00:38:36,467
Well...

478
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:39,733
I've heard that

479
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:43,067
all people are precious.

480
00:38:46,767 --> 00:38:49,096
I wish to believe

481
00:38:49,096 --> 00:38:51,467
such an absurd thing.

482
00:38:57,033 --> 00:38:58,733
Who told you

483
00:38:59,367 --> 00:39:02,433
those words?

484
00:39:02,433 --> 00:39:05,133
The one who helped me discard everything.

485
00:39:11,200 --> 00:39:14,267
These are spare clothes
for your journey to exile.

486
00:39:21,600 --> 00:39:23,433
Take care on your way.

487
00:39:29,633 --> 00:39:32,667
<i>Dying in the name of Gil Dong...</i>

488
00:39:33,567 --> 00:39:39,100
<i>The people. The name you should fear.</i>

489
00:39:39,100 --> 00:39:41,200
<i>A woman?</i>

490
00:39:41,200 --> 00:39:43,400
<i>I cherished one person...</i>

491
00:39:43,400 --> 00:39:47,367
I regret nothing about not living as a lady.

492
00:39:53,800 --> 00:39:55,667
It was you.

493
00:40:11,900 --> 00:40:13,700
You wretch.

494
00:40:18,167 --> 00:40:21,600
As Your Majesty commanded, the land
used for the hunting ground expansion

495
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:23,900
has been returned
to the people of Chungcheong,

496
00:40:23,900 --> 00:40:27,400
and all damages have been compensated.

497
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:29,367
You've worked hard.

498
00:40:30,167 --> 00:40:32,133
What else are you reading?

499
00:40:32,133 --> 00:40:33,384
I intend to discuss

500
00:40:33,384 --> 00:40:36,133
the corruption of local officials
in tomorrow's court session.

501
00:40:36,133 --> 00:40:38,967
Your Majesty hasn't slept a wink since before
and after the enthronement ceremony.

502
00:40:38,967 --> 00:40:43,200
If the king lives in comfort,
the people grow weary.

503
00:40:43,933 --> 00:40:46,167
Chief State Councilor, you may go.

504
00:40:47,131 --> 00:40:48,776
[Immediate Inspection Division]

505
00:40:51,767 --> 00:40:54,633
Your... Your Majesty!

506
00:40:54,633 --> 00:40:56,367
Your Majesty!

507
00:41:03,267 --> 00:41:05,032
Is there more work left?

508
00:41:05,032 --> 00:41:08,833
Now I just need to prepare
the herbs for tomorrow.

509
00:41:08,833 --> 00:41:11,767
You seem as though nothing ever happened.

510
00:41:11,767 --> 00:41:14,067
When I think of that day,

511
00:41:14,067 --> 00:41:16,700
my heart still races.

512
00:41:16,700 --> 00:41:19,967
How can you be so calm
after handling something so great?

513
00:41:19,967 --> 00:41:22,933
That matter is over,
so I must do my own work.

514
00:41:22,933 --> 00:41:25,967
I have never known such peace.

515
00:41:25,967 --> 00:41:28,533
I no longer have to steal.

516
00:41:32,424 --> 00:41:34,967
Why that face?

517
00:41:34,967 --> 00:41:40,967
To be honest, I was confused
when you said your souls had switched.

518
00:41:41,900 --> 00:41:47,467
I didn't know if the person
I fell for was the prince or you.

519
00:41:53,467 --> 00:41:57,233
But today, I am certain.

520
00:41:57,233 --> 00:41:58,800
It's Gil Dong.

521
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:00,533
Huh?

522
00:42:02,888 --> 00:42:05,067
Oh, you came early today.

523
00:42:05,067 --> 00:42:06,533
Give it quickly and go.

524
00:42:06,533 --> 00:42:09,700
We should go to the palace today.

525
00:42:10,967 --> 00:42:13,333
Oh, finally!

526
00:42:13,333 --> 00:42:15,567
Ah, wait!

527
00:42:15,567 --> 00:42:18,600
There's a place we need to go first.

528
00:42:20,900 --> 00:42:23,400
Why must we stop here?

529
00:42:23,400 --> 00:42:24,700
What brings you here together?

530
00:42:24,700 --> 00:42:27,067
Eun Jo is entering the palace.

531
00:42:27,067 --> 00:42:30,100
You all know what this means, right?

532
00:42:30,100 --> 00:42:31,600
What are you waiting for?

533
00:42:31,600 --> 00:42:33,100
We're closing the gibang today.

534
00:42:33,100 --> 00:42:34,800
Pardon?

535
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:38,733
What?

536
00:42:42,267 --> 00:42:45,067
There's no need to fuss over
a little nosebleed.

537
00:42:45,067 --> 00:42:46,733
If you keep this up,
you'll fall seriously ill.

538
00:42:46,733 --> 00:42:48,633
Please summon the royal physician.

539
00:42:48,633 --> 00:42:51,500
That can't be cured by any physician.

540
00:42:52,333 --> 00:42:53,767
It's lovesickness.

541
00:42:53,767 --> 00:42:55,067
You heard that, right?

542
00:42:55,067 --> 00:42:56,600
That's what he said.

543
00:42:56,600 --> 00:42:57,967
Close the book.

544
00:42:57,967 --> 00:43:00,633
The physician who can cure
you completely is here.

545
00:43:54,500 --> 00:43:56,400
Now, at last.

546
00:43:56,400 --> 00:43:59,033
- What's all this commotion?
- Huh?

547
00:43:59,033 --> 00:44:03,400
They say you haven't slept a wink
and stay in the main hall day and night.

548
00:44:03,400 --> 00:44:05,433
Oh, yeah.

549
00:44:05,433 --> 00:44:09,733
Why else would he summon me
to bring you back to your senses?

550
00:44:09,733 --> 00:44:11,933
Dae Chu told you that?

551
00:44:13,167 --> 00:44:15,433
So he's changed his master now.

552
00:44:17,300 --> 00:44:20,767
You came to bring me to my senses,

553
00:44:20,767 --> 00:44:22,967
but why are you dressed like that?

554
00:44:22,967 --> 00:44:25,133
What is wrong with it?

555
00:44:25,133 --> 00:44:26,233
It's pretty.

556
00:44:26,233 --> 00:44:28,433
It'll make me lose my senses even more.

557
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:33,533
Well, for a woman,
it's a kind of combat uniform.

558
00:44:33,533 --> 00:44:34,933
Combat?

559
00:44:34,933 --> 00:44:36,133
Did you get into a fight?

560
00:44:36,133 --> 00:44:37,300
With whom this time?

561
00:44:37,300 --> 00:44:39,133
What do you mean?

562
00:44:39,133 --> 00:44:42,133
I just said I was meeting someone.

563
00:44:42,133 --> 00:44:43,400
Meeting someone?

564
00:44:43,400 --> 00:44:45,100
Who?

565
00:44:46,033 --> 00:44:47,933
That's not the point.

566
00:44:47,933 --> 00:44:50,033
Why aren't you summoning the royal physician?

567
00:44:50,033 --> 00:44:51,167
It's important.

568
00:44:51,167 --> 00:44:54,367
So you're meeting someone
outside in a combat uniform?

569
00:44:54,367 --> 00:44:57,433
Are you even listening to me?

570
00:44:57,433 --> 00:44:58,767
Yeah, I'm listening.

571
00:44:58,767 --> 00:45:00,833
And I want to keep listening.

572
00:45:06,133 --> 00:45:08,033
But I guess you don't.

573
00:45:09,933 --> 00:45:12,300
I've been listening.

574
00:45:13,800 --> 00:45:16,067
I couldn't help but listen.

575
00:45:17,533 --> 00:45:19,267
What brings you all the way to my house?

576
00:45:19,267 --> 00:45:20,833
His Highness...

577
00:45:20,833 --> 00:45:22,000
His Majesty!

578
00:45:22,000 --> 00:45:24,100
His Majesty sent me.

579
00:45:32,033 --> 00:45:36,367
<i>The first night I spend in the palace
after sending you away.</i>

580
00:45:39,367 --> 00:45:43,433
<i>The court is in turmoil
after the sudden abdication.</i>

581
00:45:44,700 --> 00:45:47,800
<i>I am restoring Joseon,
discussing neglected affairs</i>

582
00:45:47,800 --> 00:45:50,033
<i>with the ministers.</i>

583
00:45:52,533 --> 00:45:54,984
<i>I shall not let this</i>

584
00:45:54,984 --> 00:45:57,867
<i>be wasted for the people.</i>

585
00:45:59,767 --> 00:46:01,300
<i>So, just for tonight...</i>

586
00:46:01,300 --> 00:46:05,767
<i>♫ I clasped my hands and hoped
when that moment finally found me ♫</i>

587
00:46:07,400 --> 00:46:10,967
<i>♫ Longingly treasured ♫</i>

588
00:46:10,967 --> 00:46:15,033
<i>I hope you sleep soundly without any worries.</i>

589
00:46:21,933 --> 00:46:24,667
<i>♫ All those unbearably beautiful ♫</i>

590
00:46:24,667 --> 00:46:26,667
<i>The second night.</i>

591
00:46:27,848 --> 00:46:31,033
<i>The palace is in full swing
preparing for the ceremony.</i>

592
00:46:32,833 --> 00:46:37,167
<i>♫ Turning back time to where we first met ♫</i>

593
00:46:37,167 --> 00:46:41,933
What about recalling those
banished in Gyeongo Year?

594
00:46:41,933 --> 00:46:44,033
<i>Many seek my judgment.</i>

595
00:46:44,033 --> 00:46:46,367
<i>I realize that the seat that must decide</i>

596
00:46:47,533 --> 00:46:50,667
<i>cannot be left vacant even for a moment.</i>

597
00:46:53,967 --> 00:46:55,700
<i>And</i>

598
00:46:56,733 --> 00:46:59,667
<i>so tonight again, I greet the dawn</i>

599
00:47:00,633 --> 00:47:02,667
<i>thinking of you.</i>

600
00:47:07,200 --> 00:47:08,900
<i>Only,</i>

601
00:47:10,667 --> 00:47:13,133
<i>I hope you are sleeping deeply.</i>

602
00:47:19,767 --> 00:47:21,833
<i>The third night.</i>

603
00:47:24,267 --> 00:47:26,267
<i>The fourth night.</i>

604
00:47:28,633 --> 00:47:32,300
<i>♫ I will never leave you ♫</i>

605
00:47:32,300 --> 00:47:38,567
<i>♫ The countless promises I made ♫</i>

606
00:47:38,567 --> 00:47:44,333
<i>♫ I couldn't keep ♫</i>

607
00:47:44,333 --> 00:47:46,400
<i>The fifth night.</i>

608
00:47:49,233 --> 00:47:50,967
<i>At last,</i>

609
00:47:51,800 --> 00:47:53,767
<i>the tenth night.</i>

610
00:47:55,933 --> 00:47:58,567
<i>Now, at the end of each day,</i>

611
00:47:58,567 --> 00:48:00,967
<i>I wait for the time when I count the nights.</i>

612
00:48:00,967 --> 00:48:03,033
<i>♫ You're my everything to me ♫</i>

613
00:48:03,033 --> 00:48:06,667
<i>♫ That pulled me in ♫</i>

614
00:48:06,667 --> 00:48:13,200
<i>♫ The great sunshine that is you, to me ♫</i>

615
00:48:13,200 --> 00:48:14,984
<i>The stars</i>

616
00:48:14,984 --> 00:48:18,933
<i>shine particularly deep and bright.</i>

617
00:48:20,033 --> 00:48:21,833
<i>Perhaps that is why.</i>

618
00:48:22,900 --> 00:48:25,200
<i>Every night I miss you,</i>

619
00:48:25,200 --> 00:48:27,533
<i>but tonight, even more so.</i>

620
00:48:27,533 --> 00:48:29,433
I miss you,

621
00:48:30,433 --> 00:48:31,433
Hong Eun Jo.

622
00:48:31,433 --> 00:48:35,267
<i>♫ Come in my day my everytime ♫</i>

623
00:48:35,267 --> 00:48:38,500
<i>♫ Only one ♫</i>

624
00:48:38,500 --> 00:48:46,267
<i>♫ The person who watches over me is you ♫</i>

625
00:48:49,000 --> 00:48:52,867
<i>♫ You're my everything to me ♫</i>

626
00:48:52,867 --> 00:48:56,467
<i>♫ That pulled me in ♫</i>

627
00:48:56,467 --> 00:49:03,867
<i>♫ The great sunshine that is you, to me ♫</i>

628
00:49:03,867 --> 00:49:07,533
<i>♫ You're my everything to me ♫</i>

629
00:49:07,533 --> 00:49:11,267
<i>♫ The moment I saw you again ♫</i>

630
00:49:11,267 --> 00:49:15,867
<i>♫ As if dreaming, together with you ♫</i>

631
00:49:15,867 --> 00:49:19,333
<i>♫ Again ♫</i>

632
00:49:39,167 --> 00:49:41,433
Are you sure you heard that right?

633
00:49:42,667 --> 00:49:44,333
It's stuck in my ears.

634
00:49:44,333 --> 00:49:46,100
You wrote it in every letter.

635
00:49:46,100 --> 00:49:47,900
'I miss you, I long for you.'

636
00:49:47,900 --> 00:49:50,088
I've been hearing those word
for ten days straight.

637
00:49:50,088 --> 00:49:51,533
Oh.

638
00:49:51,533 --> 00:49:53,800
So you were listening, then?

639
00:49:53,800 --> 00:49:55,200
I thought you never heard me,

640
00:49:55,200 --> 00:49:57,300
since you sent no reply.

641
00:49:59,467 --> 00:50:01,900
I was simply

642
00:50:01,900 --> 00:50:05,433
living frantically, like any commoner.

643
00:50:06,467 --> 00:50:08,367
Why are you still living so frantically?

644
00:50:08,367 --> 00:50:11,933
You're making the king's
sleepless toil meaningless.

645
00:50:12,900 --> 00:50:14,800
Exactly.

646
00:50:14,800 --> 00:50:17,000
So drink it and get some sleep.

647
00:50:17,000 --> 00:50:19,800
That's precisely why I won't drink it.

648
00:50:19,800 --> 00:50:22,000
It's been a while
since we last saw each other.

649
00:50:22,700 --> 00:50:25,033
I'll stay up all night just looking at you.

650
00:50:30,900 --> 00:50:32,733
I went to the Royal Clinic

651
00:50:32,733 --> 00:50:35,633
and carefully selected each ingredient,

652
00:50:35,633 --> 00:50:38,600
bringing these medicinal herbs
with all my heart.

653
00:50:39,667 --> 00:50:41,367
Heart?

654
00:50:43,867 --> 00:50:46,200
When did you go to the Royal Clinic?

655
00:50:48,000 --> 00:50:49,967
When our souls switched.

656
00:50:49,967 --> 00:50:54,233
I went back and forth often to prepare
herbal medicine for the Queen Dowager.

657
00:50:57,979 --> 00:50:59,500
No.

658
00:50:59,500 --> 00:51:03,967
Back then, you were still a Grand Prince,
so I could manage somehow.

659
00:51:03,967 --> 00:51:07,833
But if we switch again like this,
how could I possibly act as king?

660
00:51:23,033 --> 00:51:25,400
That won't do.

661
00:51:49,867 --> 00:51:51,400
The criminal has escaped!

662
00:51:51,400 --> 00:51:53,595
The criminal has escaped!

663
00:52:08,900 --> 00:52:10,600
Hong Eun Jo!

664
00:52:33,900 --> 00:52:36,233
Huh? You're awake?

665
00:52:41,633 --> 00:52:43,367
What's wrong?

666
00:52:54,300 --> 00:52:56,933
Did you have a bad dream?

667
00:52:57,833 --> 00:53:01,133
Did our souls switch places in your dream?

668
00:53:01,133 --> 00:53:03,200
Yeah.

669
00:53:03,200 --> 00:53:05,467
You disappeared.

670
00:53:10,033 --> 00:53:12,300
I thought something had happened to you

671
00:53:12,300 --> 00:53:15,133
and I was left alone in your body.

672
00:53:16,367 --> 00:53:18,333
What are you saying?

673
00:53:25,767 --> 00:53:27,267
Now that I think about it,

674
00:53:27,267 --> 00:53:29,500
every time our souls switched...

675
00:53:30,433 --> 00:53:33,000
It was when one of us was in grave danger.

676
00:53:38,833 --> 00:53:41,167
You knew about it?

677
00:53:46,000 --> 00:53:48,467
Why didn't you say anything?

678
00:53:49,867 --> 00:53:51,967
Because I feared you'd make this face.

679
00:53:55,100 --> 00:53:57,833
Even if it happened a hundred,
a thousand times,

680
00:53:58,900 --> 00:54:02,000
I'll run to you without hesitation.

681
00:54:03,300 --> 00:54:05,133
Until my feet gave out.

682
00:54:12,633 --> 00:54:14,633
That won't do.

683
00:54:17,133 --> 00:54:20,533
From now on, no running until your feet hurt.

684
00:54:20,533 --> 00:54:23,100
What? No?

685
00:54:23,100 --> 00:54:26,067
Yes. And one more thing.

686
00:54:26,067 --> 00:54:29,233
No more bad dreams.

687
00:54:31,707 --> 00:54:33,633
Um.

688
00:54:33,633 --> 00:54:35,667
Is there a third one?

689
00:54:36,833 --> 00:54:38,533
What is it?

690
00:54:40,467 --> 00:54:42,733
No longing.

691
00:54:42,733 --> 00:54:43,767
Why no longing?

692
00:54:43,767 --> 00:54:45,367
But it's my own longing.

693
00:54:45,367 --> 00:54:47,467
You're thirsty, aren't you?

694
00:54:47,467 --> 00:54:49,700
Here, drink this.

695
00:54:54,000 --> 00:54:55,767
Answer me.

696
00:54:56,767 --> 00:54:59,000
What?

697
00:54:59,000 --> 00:55:00,733
I already drank it.

698
00:55:03,900 --> 00:55:05,800
Now lie down.

699
00:55:23,533 --> 00:55:26,333
He already knew it, right?

700
00:55:26,333 --> 00:55:28,000
He said he hoped it wasn't true.

701
00:55:28,000 --> 00:55:29,767
And that it shouldn't be true.

702
00:55:29,767 --> 00:55:32,567
[Gangnyeongjeon Hall]
But in the end, it happened.

703
00:55:33,467 --> 00:55:37,200
If either of you is ever in danger again...

704
00:55:39,967 --> 00:55:41,633
That won't happen.

705
00:55:41,633 --> 00:55:47,000
From now on, I will protect myself
with all my strength.

706
00:55:49,933 --> 00:55:51,667
So...

707
00:55:54,867 --> 00:55:56,833
[Gangnyeongjeon Hall]

708
00:55:56,833 --> 00:55:58,733
Please protect him.

709
00:56:01,733 --> 00:56:03,400
You mean His Majesty?

710
00:56:03,400 --> 00:56:05,300
That's something I've always done.

711
00:56:05,300 --> 00:56:07,733
Beyond just my salary.

712
00:56:07,733 --> 00:56:11,167
Jeez, I should only work as much as I'm paid.

713
00:56:37,400 --> 00:56:38,933
<i>Now that I think about it,</i>

714
00:56:38,933 --> 00:56:41,233
<i>every time our souls switched...</i>

715
00:56:44,133 --> 00:56:46,800
<i>It was when one of us was in grave danger.</i>

716
00:56:49,300 --> 00:56:52,233
Were we protecting each other?

717
00:57:16,933 --> 00:57:20,367
<i>The past ten days for me
were whole and complete.</i>

718
00:57:24,000 --> 00:57:27,752
<i>Your letters asking how I was made me happy.</i>

719
00:57:32,000 --> 00:57:35,567
<i>Your reminders to sleep well felt comforting.</i>

720
00:57:38,333 --> 00:57:41,467
<i>Your complaints about missing me felt warm.</i>

721
00:57:43,867 --> 00:57:45,533
<i>So tonight,</i>

722
00:57:45,533 --> 00:57:49,367
<i>I'll take all the longing upon myself.</i>

723
00:57:51,400 --> 00:57:54,667
<i>So please, sleep peacefully.</i>

724
00:57:57,600 --> 00:57:59,833
<i>And I will</i>

725
00:57:59,833 --> 00:58:02,433
<i>long for you solely.</i>

726
00:58:06,333 --> 00:58:08,833
<i>Just deeply</i>

727
00:58:10,633 --> 00:58:12,433
<i>and for a long time.</i>

728
00:58:20,967 --> 00:58:23,333
Even if I try to stop you, you'll go, right?

729
00:58:23,333 --> 00:58:26,833
Yes, even if it's just to punish you
for being insolent.

730
00:58:26,833 --> 00:58:29,833
At least wait until dawn.

731
00:58:29,833 --> 00:58:32,367
I don't want this night to pass.

732
00:58:32,367 --> 00:58:34,200
What are you planning to do?

733
00:58:35,367 --> 00:58:37,500
My long-standing resolve.

734
00:59:31,233 --> 00:59:34,000
You ruined it all.

735
00:59:39,933 --> 00:59:41,633
Gil Dong.

736
00:59:55,567 --> 01:00:03,200
<i>♫ Like a fleeting coincidence,
you came closer to me ♫</i>

737
01:00:03,200 --> 01:00:09,800
<i>♫ Deep within my heart,
you colored me with yourself ♫</i>

738
01:00:09,800 --> 01:00:13,700
<i>♫ Even if I look without missing
a single day ♫</i>

739
01:00:13,700 --> 01:00:17,133
<i>♫ Even as I hold you before my eyes ♫</i>

740
01:00:17,133 --> 01:00:23,367
<i>♫ Yesterday, today, tomorrow,
all like a dream ♫</i>

741
01:00:23,367 --> 01:00:25,267
<i>♫ Everyday ♫</i>

742
01:00:25,267 --> 01:00:31,900
<i>♫ With just one look from you,
my heart feels like bursting ♫</i>

743
01:00:31,900 --> 01:00:33,933
<i>♫ Before I knew it,
you became my everything ♫</i>

744
01:00:33,933 --> 01:00:34,967
Step aside.

745
01:00:34,967 --> 01:00:37,000
Is Hong Eun Jo not in the palace?

746
01:00:37,000 --> 01:00:39,133
There was something
bothering me, so I went back.

747
01:00:39,133 --> 01:00:40,800
[If you want to save Gil Dong, come alone]
It was left for Your Majesty.

748
01:00:40,800 --> 01:00:42,100
Hong Eun Jo is in danger.

749
01:00:42,100 --> 01:00:43,233
I'm still the same.

750
01:00:43,233 --> 01:00:45,400
If you have foolish thoughts,
I'll stab you right here.

751
01:00:45,400 --> 01:00:47,667
And I intend to kill your mother too.

752
01:00:47,667 --> 01:00:50,733
By now, he must have received my message.

753
01:00:50,733 --> 01:00:52,200
It's Im Sa Hyeong's trap.

754
01:00:52,200 --> 01:00:54,133
I'm the one Im Sa Hyeong is after.

755
01:00:54,133 --> 01:00:58,500
If you want to save Gil Dong, come alone.

756
01:00:58,500 --> 01:00:59,600
Hong Eun Jo.

757
01:00:59,600 --> 01:01:01,333
Hong Eun Jo!
